On March 17,2020, the Chinese Academy of Sciences issued a statement refuting rumors that Shi Zhengli had claimed that the mosquito was the third host of the new coronavirus.

A statement on the website of the Wuhan Institute of Virology said that a misinformation titled "Shi Zhengli Warns In the early morning: Don't be too optimistic about the epidemic, mosquitoes or third hosts" had recently circulated on the Internet, the rumor may have a bad social impact.

Earlier, sources quoted by the media said that in the early hours of March 16, Shi Zhengli made a comprehensive analysis of the world epidemic situation. Shi Zhengli said that the current epidemic situation in China and the world is still severe, summer is just around the corner, and she's not too optimistic about ending the global epidemic by the end of April. Mosquitoes will be the new mode of transmission of coronavirus, she says.

According to the Wuhan Virus Institute statement, Shi Zhengli has never released any relevant information. Shi and the institute reserve the right to pursue the scaremongers'legal responsibilities.

According to the official website, Shi Zhengli is director of the Emerging Infectious Diseases, director of the Biosafety Working Committee and head of the emerging virus group at the Wuhan Virus Research Institute. Shi Zhengli is known as "Bat woman" , because her research in tracing the origin of SARS virus confirmed that bats are the natural host of SARS coronavirus.

After the outbreak of new Crown Pneumonia, Wuhan Virus Research Institute has become the focus of public opinion. Shi Zhengli had earlier specially refuted the rumor that "the virus is leaking from P4. " Since then, on February 15, the Internet has circulated the news that "a female graduate student of the Wuhan Virus Research Institute, Huang Mou, is patient zero of the new coronavirus pneumonia. " February 16, "Wuhan Institute of Virology Researcher Chen Mou real-name Report Wuhan Institute of Virology Director leaked the virus" News and attention.

The Chinese Academy of Sciences was established in 1956 as a comprehensive research institution specializing in basic research and related technological innovations in virology, according to the website. At present, there are 268 employees and 325 graduate students.

In response to the controversy, the Wuhan Institute of Virology published a letter to all staff and graduate students in official website on February 19. According to the letter, a number of rumors concerning the institute have been circulating on the Internet recently, causing great harm to the institute's scientific personnel and seriously disrupting the emergency scientific research mission. These rumors "have caused great harm to our scientific personnel who have been holding on to the front line of Scientific Research, and have also seriously interfered with the emergency scientific research task of the war 'epidemic' that I have undertaken. ". Looking back on the hard work we have done over the past month or so, we have no qualms about it,"the letter said.
